pikchr-rs
=========

This crate is a pure-Rust port of Pikchr, the PIC-inspired diagram language.
The pikchr-rs port itself is licensed under the MIT license (see LICENSE).

Original Pikchr
---------------
Pikchr was created by D. Richard Hipp <drh@sqlite.org> and is distributed under
the Zero-Clause BSD license. Project home: https://pikchr.org/

The source of truth for this port is the Lemon grammar file `pikchr.y` from the
upstream Pikchr repository (https://github.com/drhsqlite/pikchr). No upstream C
code is used or linked; the semantics were re-implemented in Rust by reference
to `pikchr.y`.

